=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4401013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4401013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sbu1689227118431.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sbu1689227118431.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sbu1689227118431.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tcb1665702548973\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">It is possible for the Uniface Router to automatically start Uniface Servers when the Uniface Router itself starts.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__context_w5728ab1b5b1_w5729ab1b5_w5730ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__topic_d30686e1_d30687e1_d30688e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__p_d30689e1_d30690e1_d30691e1\">This can be useful when:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__li_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1\">The server to be started is effectively a service that should always be available and that has no direct client connection.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__li_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1\">You want to have a server already available for a client the moment the client connects to the server.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__p_d30692e1_d30693e1_d30694e1\">Pre-starting servers ensures that they are available directly after rebooting the machine.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__note_w5731ab1b5b1b1b7_w5732ab1b5b1b1_w5733ab1b5b1_w5734ab1b5_w5735ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Pre-starting a server is a one-time action. The Uniface Router does not restart them if they unexpectedly exit. Such servers can be re-started by using the Uniface Router Monitor or UROUTMON component.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__p_d30695e1_d30696e1_d30697e1\">To configure the Uniface Router to automatically start Uniface Servers:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__li_d15644e1_d15645e1_d15646e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__p_d30698e1_d30699e1_d30700e1\">In the <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span> file, add\n               or edit the [PRE_START] section and define the servers to be started.  </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wpr1689227543795.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wpr1689227543795.html\" title=\"Use the [PRE_START] section to specify the Uniface Servers that the Uniface Router should automatically start. Each line specifies a server to be started and provides the same information that a client would provide when requesting a server.\">[PRE_START]</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sxr1718708960203.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sxr1718708960203.html\" title=\"Network connection strings are used to specify the network location of a Uniface Router, Uniface Server, or other server, such as SMTP or POP server. They can be used in path assignments, command line strings, and parameters to identify a target application, or to describe the current application.\">Network Connection Strings</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__p_d30701e1_d30702e1_d30703e1\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PRE_START]\nTCP:+13002|user|P@55word|server2</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tcb1665702548973__li_d15647e1_d15648e1_d15649e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Stop and restart the Uniface Router. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ztf1665702528456.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ztf1665702528456.html\" title=\"There may be occasions when you need to stop and restart the Uniface Router for system administrative purposes.\">Stop and Start the Uniface Router</a>.</span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wpr1689227543795.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[PRE_START]</a><p>Use the [PRE_START] section to specify the Uniface Servers that the Uniface Router should automatically start. Each line specifies a server to be started and provides the same information that a client would provide when requesting a server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sxr1718708960203.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Network Connection Strings</a><p>Network connection strings are used to specify the network location of a Uniface Router, Uniface Server, or other server, such as SMTP or POP server. They can be used in path assignments, command line strings, and parameters to identify a target application, or to describe the current application.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4401013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4401013\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Pre-Start Uniface Servers Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 It is possible for the Uniface Router to automatically start Uniface Servers when the Uniface Router itself starts. This can be useful when: The server to be started is effectively a service that should always be available and that has no direct client connection. You want to have a server already available for a client the moment the client connects to the server. Pre-starting servers ensures that they are available directly after rebooting the machine. Note: Pre-starting a server is a one-time action. The Uniface Router does not restart them if they unexpectedly exit. Such servers can be re-started by using the Uniface Router Monitor or UROUTMON component. To configure the Uniface Router to automatically start Uniface Servers: In the urouter.asn file, add or edit the [PRE_START] section and define the servers to be started. For more information, see [PRE_START] and Network Connection Strings . For example: [PRE_START] TCP:+13002|user|P@55word|server2 Copy Stop and restart the Uniface Router. For more information, see Stop and Start the Uniface Router . Related Links [PRE_START] Use the [PRE_START] section to specify the Uniface Servers that the Uniface Router should automatically start. Each line specifies a server to be started and provides the same information that a client would provide when requesting a server. Network Connection Strings Network connection strings are used to specify the network location of a Uniface Router, Uniface Server, or other server, such as SMTP or POP server. They can be used in path assignments, command line strings, and parameters to identify a target application, or to describe the current application. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}